
  <sn><md>### Soil Temperature

Temperature is the condition of a body that determines the transfer of heat to or from other bodies. **Soil temperature** refers to the `thermal condition of the soil body` which governs the direction and rate of heat flow. It is measured in degrees and is one of the essential plant-growth factors just like water, air and nutrients.

Soil temperature controls **seed germination**, **root development**, and **overall plant growth**. It also influences soil **moisture**, **aeration**, **structure**, **microbial and enzyme activities**, **decomposition of residues**, and **availability of plant nutrients**.
It varies due to changes in radiant, thermal and latent heat-exchange processes occurring primarily at the soil surface.
